"title": "2545: Jesus Christ, opposition to",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2545",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ encountered criticism, grumbling and plotting because he was seen as a threat to the religious and political hierarchy, and because he exposed sin.</p>\n<h2>Opposition by different groups</h2>\n<h3>By family and friends</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:24-Luke4:29\">LUK 4:24–4:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:55-Matt13:57\">MAT 13:55–13:57</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:3-Mark6:4\">MRK 6:3–6:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:21\">MRK 3:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:3-John7:5\">JHN 7:3–7:5</a></p>\n<h3>By religious leaders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:14\">MAT 12:14</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:6\">MRK 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:11\">LUK 6:11</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:47-John11:53\">JHN 11:47–11:53</a></p>\n<h3>By political leaders</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:13-Matt2:14\">MAT 2:13–2:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:31\">LUK 13:31</a></p>\n<h2>Opposition through criticism and accusation</h2>\n<h3>Criticism of Jesus Christ's choice of company</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:11\">MAT 9:11</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:16\">MRK 2:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:30\">LUK 5:30</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:39\">LUK 7:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:7\">LUK 19:7</a></p>\n<h3>Criticism for breaking with tradition</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:1-Matt15:2\">MAT 15:1–15:2</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:5\">MRK 7:5</a> <em>Though criticism is directed at the disciples, it is really against Jesus Christ</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:16\">LUK 10:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:38\">LUK 11:38</a></p>\n<h3>Accusations of Sabbath-breaking</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:16\">JHN 5:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:2\">MAT 12:2</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:24\">MRK 2:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:2\">LUK 6:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:10\">MAT 12:10</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:2\">MRK 3:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:7\">LUK 6:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:14\">LUK 13:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:1\">LUK 14:1</a></p>\n<h3>Accusations of blasphemy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:33\">JHN 10:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:3\">MAT 9:3</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:6-Mark2:7\">MRK 2:6–2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:21\">LUK 5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:65\">MAT 26:65</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:64\">MRK 14:64</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:18\">JHN 5:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:36\">JHN 10:36</a></p>\n<h3>Accusations of being demon-possessed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:20\">JHN 10:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:24\">MAT 12:24</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:22\">MRK 3:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:15\">LUK 11:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:20\">JHN 7:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:48\">JHN 8:48</a></p>\n<h2>Reasons for opposing Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Because of hatred</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:23-John15:25\">JHN 15:23–15:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:7\">JHN 7:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:40\">JHN 8:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:18\">JHN 15:18</a></p>\n<h3>Because people's minds are closed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:43-John8:44\">JHN 8:43–8:44</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:37\">JHN 8:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:4\">2CO 4:4</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ knew where opposition would lead</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:21\">MAT 16:21</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:31-Mark8:32\">MRK 8:31–8:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:22\">LUK 9:22</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:22-Matt17:23\">MAT 17:22–17:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:31\">MRK 9:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:17-Matt20:19\">MAT 20:17–20:19</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:32-Mark10:34\">MRK 10:32–10:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:31-Luke18:32\">LUK 18:31–18:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:44\">LUK 9:44</a></p>\n<h2>Unsuccessful opposition before the crucifixion</h2>\n<h3>Early attempts to arrest Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:39\">JHN 10:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:30\">JHN 7:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:32\">JHN 7:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:44\">JHN 7:44</a></p>\n<h3>Attempts on Jesus Christ's life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:59\">JHN 8:59</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:28-Luke4:30\">LUK 4:28–4:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:19\">JHN 7:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:31\">JHN 10:31</a></p>\n<h2>Opposition that led to the crucifixion</h2>\n<h3>Plots by the Jewish leaders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:3-Matt26:4\">MAT 26:3–26:4</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:1-Mark14:2\">MRK 14:1–14:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:2\">LUK 22:2</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:46\">MAT 21:46</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:12\">MRK 12:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:19\">LUK 20:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:57\">JHN 11:57</a></p>\n<h3>The chief priests stirred up the crowd</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:20-Matt27:23\">MAT 27:20–27:23</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:11-Mark15:14\">MRK 15:11–15:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:21\">LUK 23:21</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:15\">JHN 19:15</a></p>\n<h3>Rejection by political authorities</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:26\">MAT 27:26</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:15\">MRK 15:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:24-Luke23:25\">LUK 23:24–23:25</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:7-Luke23:12\">LUK 23:7–23:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:16\">JHN 19:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:25-Acts4:27\">ACT 4:25–4:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:1-Ps2:2\">PSA 2:1–2:2</a></p>\n<h3>The mockery of the Roman soldiers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:27-Matt27:31\">MAT 27:27–27:31</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:16-Mark15:20\">MRK 15:16–15:20</a></p>\n<h3>The betrayal by Judas Iscariot</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:14-Matt26:16\">MAT 26:14–26:16</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:10-Mark14:11\">MRK 14:10–14:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:3-Luke22:6\">LUK 22:3–22:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:47-Matt26:50\">MAT 26:47–26:50</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:43-Mark14:45\">MRK 14:43–14:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:47-Luke22:48\">LUK 22:47–22:48</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:2-John18:5\">JHN 18:2–18:5</a></p>\n<h2>Opposition at the crucifixion</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:39-Matt27:44\">MAT 27:39–27:44</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:29-Mark15:32\">MRK 15:29–15:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:35-Luke23:39\">LUK 23:35–23:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:21\">JHN 19:21</a></p>\n<h2>Opposition to Jesus Christ in apostolic preaching</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:13-Acts3:15\">ACT 3:13–3:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:23\">ACT 2:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:10\">ACT 4:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:30\">ACT 5:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:52-Acts7:53\">ACT 7:52–7:53</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:39\">ACT 10:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:27-Acts13:29\">ACT 13:27–13:29</a></p>\n<h2>Saul of Tarsus opposes Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:4-Acts9:5\">ACT 9:4–9:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:7-Acts22:8\">ACT 22:7–22:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:14-Acts26:15\">ACT 26:14–26:15</a></p>",
